16 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Procurement of food products -- rulemaking -- reporting. (1) Food
17 products produced in the state may be procured either by standard procedures or by direct purchase. Montana-
18 produced food products may be procured by direct purchase when:
19 (a) the quality of available Montana-produced food products is substantially equivalent to the
20 quality of similar food products produced outside the state;
21 (b) a vender is able to supply Montana-produced food products in sufficient quantity; and
22 (c) a bid for Montana-produced food products either does not exceed or reasonably exceeds the
23 lowest bid or price quoted for similar products produced outside the state. A bid reasonably exceeds the lowest
24 bid or price quoted when, in the discretion of the person charged by law with the duty to purchase food products
25 for a governmental body, the higher bid is reasonable and capable of being paid out of that governmental
26 body's existing budget without any further supplemental or additional appropriation.
27 (2) The department shall adopt any rules necessary to administer the optional procurement
28 exception and reporting requirement established in this section.
